  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 6 critical, 19 high, 9 medium, 5 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) and Cluj Avram Iancu (CLJ/LRCL); plus 22 other bases. 9 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, thunderstorm / convective risk and low cloud base  — most notably around Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD). Network hotspots: Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Lublin (LUZ/EPLB), Modlin (WMI/EPMO), Warsaw Chopin (WAW/EPWA) and 8 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Lublin (LUZ/EPLB) and 9 others.",
